        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-31T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-12-31T13:00:00-05:00" n="688" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d688">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Korea/12–3147: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in El Salvador</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-12-31T13:00:00-05:00">December 31, 1947—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>162. Seek early interview with FonMin to express high importance attached by US
                    Govt to Salvadoran participation in work of United Nations Temporary Commission
                    on Korea. Failure of El Salvador to participate in work of Commission would be
                    severe blow to functioning United Nations and would be subject to
                    misinterpretation and misleading propaganda by elements not interested in early
                    peaceful settlement Korean situation.</p>
                <p>For your information Salvadoran Amb<note n="8" xml:id="d688fn8">Dr. Héctor David
                        Castro.</note> in Washington is communicating with his Govt along same
                    lines.</p>
                <p>Telegraph urgently decision Salvadoran Govt re participation Korean
                    Commission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
